The paper proposes a deep neural network for person re-identification, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on learning high-level features and similarity metrics, which are core topics in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of adaptive RMSProp gradient descent algorithm, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on large datasets, which is a common practice in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
